The paper discusses the role of context in perception and cognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a new process model for cognitive hierarchies, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper demonstrates a novel approach to object tracking using context, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
